  'p2': {title:'Pillar II: Food security & health', desc:'4 synergies identified. ACS bridges WFP/FAO local procurement with trade facilitation, channels Member State agricultural cooperation, advocates to CDB/CAF for smallholder finance, and convenes integrated school feeding + protection pilots.'},
  'p3': {title:'Pillar III: WASH', desc:'3 synergies identified. ACS facilitates Caribbean water authority twinning, mobilizes CARPHA epidemiological surge capacity, and promotes gender-sensitive WASH design standards across the humanitarian response.'},
  'p4': {title:'Pillar IV: Child protection & vulnerable groups', desc:'4 synergies identified. ACS brokers pre-positioning warehouse agreements, designs integrated education-protection pilots in development hubs, promotes cross-border safeguarding protocols, and manages a regional professional roster.'},
  'p5': {title:'Pillar V: Rapid & flexible financing', desc:'5 synergies identified. ACS hosts a donor coordination dashboard, connects diaspora communities to Haiti\u2019s cooperation fund, amplifies multi-year financing advocacy in regional fora, advocates for CCRIF integration, and facilitates mobile money regulatory exchanges.'},
  'p6': {title:'Pillar VI: Transition to sustainable development', desc:'5 synergies identified. ACS matchmakes institutional twinning, establishes development hub coordination frameworks, advocates for Caribbean trade preferences, channels digitalization expertise, and bridges CARICOM and Latin American cooperation offers.'},
  'cc-1': {title:'CC-1: 4Ws mapping', desc:'OCHA information management + ACS Secretariat. ACS extends humanitarian data with development, bilateral, and private-sector intervention layers. Part of the information architecture cluster.'},
  'cc-2': {title:'CC-2: Focal points liaison', desc:'BINUH/UN Country Team + ACS Steering Committee focal points. ACS channels Member State bilateral offers into the UN-coordinated framework, avoiding parallel tracks.'},
  'cc-3': {title:'CC-3: Anticipatory action', desc:'CERF anticipatory framework + ACS DRR Committee early warning systems. ACS regional early warning data feeds into Haiti\u2019s CERF trigger mechanisms for pre-impact response.'},
  'p1-1': {title:'P1-1: Access advocacy', desc:'OCHA access negotiations + ACS political convening. Steering Committee statements reinforce humanitarian principles and sensitize security forces on neutrality and impartiality.'},
  'p1-2': {title:'P1-2: Capacity mapping', desc:'IFRC local Red Cross networks + ACS 4Ws territorial layer. Maps which local organizations have established access in specific zones for delivery planning.'},
  'p1-3': {title:'P1-3: Security data brokerage', desc:'ACLED conflict data + ACAPS analysis + ACS satellite/early warning. ACS brokers security information through OCHA\u2019s confidential channels for route planning.'},
  'p1-4': {title:'P1-4: Private logistics mapping', desc:'Private sector distribution chains + ACS trade networks. Maps commercial logistics still operating in contested territories for humanitarian use.'},
  'p2-1': {title:'P2-1: Local procurement linkage', desc:'WFP/FAO procurement mandates + ACS trade facilitation. Connects Haitian producers to WFP procurement systems and facilitates triangular cooperation.'},
  'p2-2': {title:'P2-2: Agricultural input coordination', desc:'FAO programs (seeds, tools, livestock) + ACS bilateral agricultural cooperation from Member States. Coordinates aid into shared geographic zones.'},
  'p2-3': {title:'P2-3: Agricultural finance advocacy', desc:'WG2 crop insurance/contract farming recommendations + CDB/CAF/IDB engagement. ACS presents consolidated advocacy to development banks. Part of financial advocacy cluster.'},
  'p2-4': {title:'P2-4: School feeding + protection', desc:'WFP school feeding + UNICEF child protection + Member State resources. ACS convenes integrated pilot in Cap-Ha\u00eftien or Les Cayes. Part of geographic convergence cluster.'},
  'p3-1': {title:'P3-1: Community WASH twinning', desc:'UNICEF WASH programs + Caribbean municipal water authorities. ACS facilitates twinning on community-managed sanitation models. Part of South-South cooperation cluster.'},
  'p3-2': {title:'P3-2: Cholera surge response', desc:'PAHO surveillance + CARPHA epidemiological capacity. ACS mobilizes Caribbean public health surge support. Part of South-South cooperation cluster.'},
  'p3-3': {title:'P3-3: Gender-sensitive WASH standards', desc:'Protection actors + WASH actors. ACS promotes unified design standards for safe, sex-segregated sanitation in displacement sites.'},
  'p4-1': {title:'P4-1: Supply pre-positioning', desc:'UNICEF supply needs + ACS Member State warehouses. ACS brokers agreements with Panama, Dominican Republic, Jamaica for fast-track customs.'},
  'p4-2': {title:'P4-2: Education-protection pilot', desc:'WFP + UNICEF + Member State technical cooperation. Integrated demonstration project outside Port-au-Prince. Part of geographic convergence cluster.'},
  'p4-3': {title:'P4-3: Cross-border safeguarding', desc:'Child protection agencies + Caribbean transit states. ACS promotes harmonized protocols for Haitian children moving via irregular maritime routes.'},
  'p4-4': {title:'P4-4: Professional roster', desc:'UNICEF/IOM + francophone/Creole-speaking Member States. ACS manages regional roster for rotational surge deployments. Part of South-South cooperation cluster.'},
  'p5-1': {title:'P5-1: Donor coordination dashboard', desc:'OCHA Financial Tracking Service + ACS Secretariat + Haiti Ministry of Planning. ACS hosts coordination platform tracking humanitarian and development flows. Part of information architecture cluster.'},
  'p5-2': {title:'P5-2: Diaspora engagement', desc:'Haiti Ministry of Planning cooperation fund + ACS networks in states hosting Haitian diaspora. Connects community organizations to structured investment mechanisms.'},
  'p5-3': {title:'P5-3: Multi-year financing advocacy', desc:'World Bank CPF + ACS Member States\u2019 collective voice. Joint advocacy at CARICOM, OAS, IDB for 5-10 year financing commitments. Part of financial advocacy cluster.'},
